olive oil
½ tin sweetcorn
3 clove garlic
1 carrot
1 packet beef strips
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet garlic aioli
1 tsp white wine vinegar
8 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 bag coriander
1 sachet Tex-Mex spice blend
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese

• Drain sweetcorn (see ingredients). Finely chop garlic. Grate carrot.
• In a large bowl, combine the garlic, Tex-Mex spice blend and a drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper, then add beef strips and toss to coat. Set aside.
• Heat a large frying pan over a high heat. Cook sweetcorn until lightly charred, 4-5 minutes. Transfer to a bowl and season.

TIP: Cover the pan with a lid if the corn kernels are “popping” out.

• Return pan to a high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. When oil is hot, cook beef strips until browned and cooked through, 1-2 minutes.

TIP: If your pan is getting crowded, cook in batches for the best results!

• In a medium bowl, combine carrot, shredded cabbage mix, garlic aioli and white wine vinegar. Season and toss to coat.
• Microwave mini flour tortillas on a plate for 10 second bursts, or until warmed through.

• Roughly chop coriander.
• Top each tortilla with creamy slaw, charred sweetcorn, Tex-Mex beef and shredded Cheddar cheese.
• Serve garnished with coriander.